T*
(Student Name: Mason Carter \(Fictional\)    DOB: 2016-09-03    Student ID: 447219) Tj
T*
(Primary Language: English    Disability Eligibility: Specific Learning Disability, Speech/Language Impairment) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1\) PRESENT LEVELS OF ACADEMIC ACHIEVEMENT AND FUNCTIONAL PERFORMANCE \(PLAAFP\)) Tj
T*
(Reading: Mason reads at approximately a late Grade 2 instructional level. On district benchmark passages,) Tj
T*
(he answers literal comprehension questions with 72% accuracy and inferential questions with 44% accuracy.) Tj
T*
(He benefits from pre-teaching vocabulary, chunked text, and visual supports.) Tj
T*
(Written Expression: Mason writes simple 3-4 sentence responses with inconsistent capitalization, punctuation,) Tj
T*
(and sentence expansion. He often omits supporting details and needs frequent prompting to revise.) Tj
T*
(Mathematics: Mason demonstrates grade-level strength in basic computation \(addition/subtraction facts at 90%\),) Tj
T*
(but needs support with multi-step word problems and explaining mathematical reasoning in writing.) Tj
T*
(Communication: Mason exhibits mild articulation errors with /r/ and /th/ in connected speech and occasional) Tj
T*
(difficulty organizing verbal responses during class discussions.) Tj
T*
(Functional/Behavioral: Mason follows classroom routines with one prompt and is respectful with peers/adults.) Tj
T*
(When tasks are text-heavy, he may avoid work or rush. Breaks and clear checklists improve engagement.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2\) PARENT CONCERNS) Tj
T*
(Parents report concern that reading demands across content areas are increasing faster than current supports.) Tj
T*
(They request measurable goals, explicit progress reporting, and consistent accommodations in all classes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3\) MEASURABLE ANNUAL GOALS) Tj
T*
(Goal 1 - Reading Comprehension:) Tj
T*
(Baseline: On grade-level passages, Mason currently answers inferential comprehension questions with 44% accuracy.) Tj
T*
(Annual Goal: By 2027-03-14, given grade-level narrative and informational passages and a graphic organizer,) Tj
T*
(Mason will answer inferential comprehension questions with at least 80% accuracy across 3 consecutive probes.) Tj
T*
(Progress Monitoring: Curriculum-based probes biweekly, teacher data sheets, and quarterly benchmark review.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Goal 2 - Written Expression:) Tj
T*
(Baseline: Mason writes a 4-sentence paragraph with complete sentence conventions in 1 of 5 samples.) Tj
T*
(Annual Goal: By 2027-03-14, Mason will compose a 6-8 sentence paragraph including topic sentence, 3+ details,) Tj
T*
(and correct capitalization/punctuation in 4 of 5 writing samples using a rubric score of at least 3/4.) Tj
T*
(Progress Monitoring: Monthly writing prompt with rubric scoring and work sample portfolio review.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Goal 3 - Speech Sound Production:) Tj
T*
(Baseline: Mason produces target /r/ and /th/ sounds with 55% accuracy in connected speech.) Tj
T*
(Annual Goal: By 2027-03-14, Mason will produce /r/ and /th/ in structured conversation with 85% accuracy) Tj
T*
(over 3 consecutive therapy data collections.) Tj
T*
(Progress Monitoring: SLP data collection during weekly sessions and classroom carryover checks.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4\) SPECIAL EDUCATION, RELATED SERVICES, AND SUPPLEMENTARY AIDS) Tj
T*
(Specialized Academic Instruction \(Reading/Writing\): 300 minutes per week, small-group, general education push-in) Tj
T*
